results.abstract: France-Amerique, American edition of conservative French newspaper Le Figaro shares cramped New York City office with V Novom Svete, American edition of Moscow newspaper Moscovsky Komsomolets; Russian paper competes with over 30 other newspapers in city serving growing audience of Russian-speaking Americans; French paper faces little competition; photo (M)

results.lead_paragraph: On the surface, it seems an odd coupling. Sharing a single, cramped office in the Actors Equity Building at 46th Street and Broadway are two vastly different newspapers serving two distinct communities. One, France-Amerique, the American edition of the conservative French newspaper Le Figaro, is staid and somewhat literary, with a word-filled cover. An interview with Norman Mailer was featured on the front page of a recent issue.
